# Local Business Platform - Master Rule Index

This document serves as the central index for all active Cursor rules within this repository, organized by category. These rules define processes, structures, and guidelines for development.

## 🚨 CORE DEVELOPMENT PRINCIPLE

**ALWAYS EDIT EXISTING FILES RATHER THAN CREATING NEW ONES**

This is the fundamental rule that applies across ALL development work:
- Search for existing files with similar functionality first
- Extend or modify existing files instead of creating new ones
- Only create new files when absolutely no existing file can serve the purpose
- Never create backup, copy, example, or demo versions of files

### Non-negotiable workflow: Move, don't recreate

- Use `git mv` when reorganizing or renaming files to preserve history
- After moves, update imports/links/aliases and validate references
- Avoid content copy-paste; prefer relocations with tracked history

